title: About
text:
I grew on up in a town by the outskirts of Boston, MA. Looking at a map, this town that’s south of Boston is known as Randolph, but if you were to ask me, I’d call it home. Born in Boston and raised in Randolph, I can confidently say I’m native to Massachusetts, well, at least not until my exposure to western Mass where I attended college at UMass Amherst.
Growing up with Randolph’s public school system made me appreciate the diversity I was exposed to at an early age.
I don’t often update my linkedin… www.linkedin.com/in/michellele2002

title: Home Page
text: Hi, I’m Michelle Le and welcome to my personal website. I’ve created this website through coding skills I’ve honed during two semesters of bioinformatics at my Alma mater, UMass Amherst. No, my major wasn’t in computer science if that’s what you’re wondering. I currently have a B.S in biology, but I choose to code on the side as a fun little hobby. Click here to learn more about me.
